    # Generate universe variables
#   * temperature subjective ranges [19, 24]
#   * CO2 subjective ranges [300, 1300]
#   * PIR subjective ranges [0, 1]
#   * light subjective ranges [0, 600]



x_temperature = data_df['MeanTemp'].values
# x_temperature2 = data_df['S2Temp'].values
# x_temperature3 = data_df['S3Temp'].values
x_CO2 = data_df['CO2'].values
x_PIR = data_df['PIR'].values
#x_PIR2 = data_df['PIR2'].values
x_light = data_df['MeanLight'].values


min = x_temperature.min()
max = x_temperature.max()
med = min+((max-min)/2)

# Generate fuzzy membership functions
x_temperature_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature , [min, min, med])
temperature_md = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature , [min, med, max])
temperature_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature , [med, max, max])

# temperature2_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature2 , [19, 19, 24])
# temperature2_md = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature2 , [19, 24, 24])
# temperature2_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature2 , [24, 24, 24])

# temperature3_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature3 , [19, 19, 24])
# temperature3_md = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature3 , [19, 24, 24])
# temperature3_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_temperature3 , [24, 24, 24])

min = x_CO2.min()
max = x_CO2.max()
med = min+((max-min)/2)

CO2_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_CO2 , [min, min, med])
CO2_md = fuzz.trimf(x_CO2 , [min, med, max])
CO2_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_CO2 , [med, max, max])

min = x_PIR.min()
max = x_PIR.max()
med = min+((max-min)/2)


# PIR n faz sentido transformar em fuzzy set pq é um crisp set. ou está on ou off .. imo
# PIR_on = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR , [min, min, med])
# PIR_off = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR , [min, med, max])
# PIR_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR , [med, max, max])

# PIR2_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR2 , [0, 0, 1])
# PIR2_md = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR2 , [0, 1, 1])
# PIR2_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_PIR2 , [1, 1, 1])

min = x_light.min()
max=x_light.max()
med = min+((max-min)/2)
light1_lo = fuzz.trimf(x_light , [min, min, med])
light1_md = fuzz.trimf(x_light , [min, med, max])
light1_hi = fuzz.trimf(x_light , [med, max, max])


# Visualize these universes and membership functions
fig, (ax0, ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=3, figsize=(20,10))

ax0.plot(x_temperature, x_temperature_lo, 'b', linewidth=1.5, label='Low')
ax0.plot(x_temperature, temperature_md, 'g', linewidth=1.5, label='Medium')
ax0.plot(x_temperature, temperature_hi, 'r', linewidth=1.5, label='High')
ax0.set_title('Temperature1')
ax0.legend()

ax1.plot(x_CO2, CO2_lo, 'b', linewidth=1.5, label='Low')
ax1.plot(x_CO2, CO2_md, 'g', linewidth=1.5, label='Medium')
ax1.plot(x_CO2, CO2_hi, 'r', linewidth=1.5, label='High')
ax1.set_title('CO2')
ax1.legend()

ax2.plot(x_light, light1_lo, 'b', linewidth=1.5, label='Low')
ax2.plot(x_light, light1_md, 'g', linewidth=1.5, label='Medium')
ax2.plot(x_light, light1_hi, 'r', linewidth=1.5, label='High')
ax2.set_title('Light')
ax2.legend()


# Turn off top/right axes
for ax in (ax0, ax1, ax2):
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax.get_xaxis().tick_bottom()
    ax.get_yaxis().tick_left()

plt.tight_layout()
